race.comment: GEM TYCOON (2) is a Written Tycoon gelding on debut for the sharp Bjorn Baker stable. Has trialled well in readiness and draws well. Expect to see Chambers plant on her speed and prove hard to stop. WILLINGHAM (3) returns a gelding for the Waterhouse & Bott stable. Was good on debut at Geelong back in June, if he's improved off that he will take some running down. ZOUGOTME (6) returns for the R & L Price camp and looks to have come on a treat during the break, chasing Inglis Nursery winner, Where's The Circus to the line in recent trial. Expect him to drift back from the draw and be saved for the final shot at them. BOLD ALLIANCE (11) is knocking on the door and carries a fitness edge. Don't take lightly. ZOUSTRONG (1) is a likely improver worth including in exotics.
